Xqj6sT5lOyf6a1jxyhGjSZpcSFIJIGNah-wJ_lJinTfX5Wz-pfgBw2c3F6PBcib10O_FAgetz2RhTj5ih6MrXPinIUwz0Kxqml9wfkWqSHbep4OUUvSw9TSeo4SMacutmC0GsCDIbVZ9yj1JtmyYaFyIEqDoGUos0OmTO3G1vCX_ViMB-9rrNyRx0IgniFKjsQCt8wHgdIP2Gh3gfJ5tVN6uEhXrXFklDU2Lvi16YvBJZlacL0Y1Fg5-7zHn_PJ4xUuPy2xd0hOSeatDvvmqQdUd8NZaotLj8qQ6BVpC5vlrqGlGMEMaE5OIgXGOCCVGfYl-PJuOmcreZ0TI55v8z8PfILXXKZIEiIAuebCFS-gj0lhZMvG0QVAMBdoCcky66DUC9WHp2EPA1icQeFawqjuD9Xvi_lFIXD5yKFQuuAUx_UE6aEvbFqjQFBeJz9SUkGWHuOv6O_3xy_RXnq6u6UeJO4iCBEZCrw57KJzAO00SpZ29uIEpnA9i6Mp1rDNN0PeFhE70cnsonjTx28SFBK5aGJQA_8ZtUzrHohGJIGWYHUVtslxDTPLrYK3_GxmR1vQvFCaa5wKz7JeZH1dYF0Swc5jWhcyuJiX0aj1pjsbRcIeB4sJn4kI8I2ndZMXb-YBOKQEAAPHWLIvy3CkQPLWAJq8U2bPd-gni3i1SqL2pf-O50IH6QdFV5PBQBxEzFZqU4CDXcZesUH52x_e92_ceK4hr7-EChzjDjUon7lCTQ2-Yx8Jf9j-1v7gmBISS5-HyYKGY-J2ou_Z8ydCw6n2XfR1o1ATBdvRBz6WIXr_3UvcS08rIZ-65SFjo-fKH1oWSYBJtKYiHrJfllb3cc3i0DE75IT473urPAyhh9hQ9f2r59FXjhU6jJFszDBkvqCFPqAC-rcdO821RtPmHueuRqolrA6obDMSjY_UXpSTAb5MZcO8y2BnwOzDOk3kNCtNfvLiqj_mPen3gBz8e6n51PsRBBV9xoTlkIjVJZfigIHBCzpNozob_1IrprzQgZlz8rGq489pyhV\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating metadata generation**\\n\\nI'm considering whether changing active library metadata will impact how metadata is recorded for tests. It could be possible, but it seems that a conditional agent would work. The task emphasizes focusing on the active class, and adding test package support for the helper definitely relates to that. It seems like the dynamic report target may only need to call active sites, where filtering isn't a concern. I might need to include the test package and explore the existing source context to see if there's anything useful there.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing ClassLoader behavior**\\n\\nI’m looking at the report regarding `ClassLoader#getResourceAsStream` on line 61, which seems to indicate that instrumentation records method invocations regardless of whether a resource file exists. I’m considering overriding `getResources` to return a memory URL, which aligns with existing practices. The property string could target a nested factory, and I wonder if we can override `loadClass`. If we don't, the parent will load the nested class by name, but the custom class loader will inherit and delegate the `loadClass` call. That seems promising!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Creating a factory class**\\n\\nI need to create a factory class that extends AbstractCompilerFactory. This class should be public, static, and final, and it has to implement the `newCompiler()` method since it's abstract. The method can return an unsupported message, similar to the way other abstract methods handle it. I should also remember to import necessary components like ICompiler, AbstractCompilerFactory, ICompilerFactory, and CompilerFactoryFactory to ensure everything works properly. Let's get this set up!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring dynamic loading**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the concept of \\\"open-ended dynamic loading.\\\" It seems to load existing image classes rather than class definitions after the build process. This looks good, and I don't need to catch any errors here. Next, I realize I need to add a filter to refine the process, so I'll use an edit function to implement that. It feels like I'm on the right track with this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_C1XrObBGJyhZyoqqKNJ0dC4I|fc_05cf16ffcf80d3270169f93bfd64dc8197ab6496b42d11dda3", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.codehaus.janino/commons-compiler/3.0.16/src/test/java/org_codehaus_janino/commons_compiler/CompilerFactoryFactoryTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_codehaus_janino.commons_compiler;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLConnection;\nimport java.net.URLStreamHandler;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\n\nimport org.codehaus.commons.compiler.AbstractCompilerFactory;\nimport org.codehaus.commons.compiler.CompilerFactoryFactory;\nimport org.codehaus.commons.compiler.ICompiler;\nimport org.codehaus.commons.compiler.ICompilerFactory;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class CompilerFactoryFactoryTest {\n    private static final String PROPERTIES_RESOURCE_NAME = \"org.codehaus.commons.compiler.properties\";\n    private static final String TEST_FACTORY_ID = \"test-compiler-factory\";\n    private static final byte[] FACTORY_CONFIGURATION = (\"compilerFactory=\"\n            + TestCompilerFactory.class.getName() + System.lineSeparator()).getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n\n    @Test\n    void discoversCompilerFactoriesFromContextClassLoaderResources() throws Exception {\n        ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        ClassLoader resourceClassLoader = new ResourceBackedClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(resourceClassLoader);\n\n            ICompilerFactory namedFactory = CompilerFactoryFactory.getCompilerFactory(\n                    TestCompilerFactory.class.getName());\n            ICompilerFactory[] discoveredFactories = CompilerFactoryFactory.getAllCompilerFactories();\n            ICompilerFactory defaultFactory = CompilerFactoryFactory.getDefaultCompilerFactory();\n\n            assertThat(namedFactory).isInstanceOf(TestCompilerFactory.class);\n            assertThat(discoveredFactories).hasSize(1);\n            assertThat(discoveredFactories[0]).isInstanceOf(TestCompilerFactory.class);\n            assertThat(defaultFactory).isInstanceOf(TestCompilerFactory.class);\n            assertThat(defaultFactory.getId()).isEqualTo(TEST_FACTORY_ID);\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class TestCompilerFactory extends AbstractCompilerFactory {\n        public TestCompilerFactory() {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String getId() {\n            return TEST_FACTORY_ID;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String toString() {\n            return \"test compiler factory\";\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String getImplementationVersion() {\n            return \"test\";\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public ICompiler newCompiler() {\n            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(getId() + \": newCompiler\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ResourceBackedClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private ResourceBackedClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public InputStream getResourceAsStream(String name) {\n            if (!PROPERTIES_RESOURCE_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.getResourceAsStream(name);\n            }\n            return new ByteArrayInputStream(FACTORY_CONFIGURATION);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Enumeration<URL> getResources(String name) throws IOException {\n            if (!PROPERTIES_RESOURCE_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.getResources(name);\n            }\n            return Collections.enumeration(Collections.singletonList(resourceUrl()));\n        }\n\n        private URL resourceUrl() throws IOException {\n            return new URL(null, \"memory:commons-compiler-factory\", new URLStreamHandler() {\n                @Override\n                protected URLConnection openConnection(URL url) {\n                    return new URLConnection(url) {\n                        @Override\n                        public void connect() {\n 